<li><span class="citation" id="CITEREFWang2008"><a href="/wiki/Wang_Li_(linguist)" title="Wang Li (linguist)">Wang, Li</a> (2008) (in Chinese), <i>Hànyǔ Yǔyīn Shǐ 汉语语音史</i>, Beijing: <i>Shāngwù Yìnshūguǎn Chūbǎn</i>, <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-7-100-05390-7" title="Special:BookSources/978-7-100-05390-7">978-7-100-05390-7</a>.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=H%C3%A0ny%C7%94+Y%C7%94y%C4%ABn+Sh%C7%90+%E6%B1%89%E8%AF%AD%E8%AF%AD%E9%9F%B3%E5%8F%B2&amp;rft.aulast=Wang&amp;rft.aufirst=Li&amp;rft.au=Wang%2C%26%2332%3BLi&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.place=Beijing&amp;rft.pub=%27%27Sh%C4%81ngw%C3%B9+Y%C3%ACnsh%C5%ABgu%C7%8En+Ch%C5%ABb%C7%8En%27%27&amp;rft.isbn=978-7-100-05390-7&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Old_Chinese"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><span class="citation" id="CITEREFWilkinson2000">Wilkinson, Endymion (2000), <i>Chinese history: a manual</i> (2nd ed.), Harvard Univ Asia Center, <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-67400249-4" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-67400249-4">978-0-67400249-4</a>.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Chinese+history%3A+a+manual&amp;rft.aulast=Wilkinson&amp;rft.aufirst=Endymion&amp;rft.au=Wilkinson%2C%26%2332%3BEndymion&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.edition=2nd&amp;rft.pub=Harvard+Univ+Asia+Center&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-67400249-4&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Old_Chinese"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><span class="citation" id="CITEREFZhengzhang1991">Zhengzhang, Shangfang 郑张尚芳 (1991), "Decipherment of <i>Yue-Ren-Ge</i> (Song of the Yue boatman)", <i>Cahiers de Linguistique – Asie Orientale</i> <b>20</b> (2): 159–168, <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.3406%2Fclao.1991.1345" class="external text" rel="nofollow">10.3406/clao.1991.1345</a>.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Decipherment+of+%27%27Yue-Ren-Ge%27%27+%28Song+of+the+Yue+boatman%29&amp;rft.jtitle=Cahiers+de+Linguistique+%E2%80%93+Asie+Orientale&amp;rft.aulast=Zhengzhang&amp;rft.aufirst=Shangfang+%E9%83%91%E5%BC%A0%E5%B0%9A%E8%8A%B3&amp;rft.au=Zhengzhang%2C%26%2332%3BShangfang+%E9%83%91%E5%BC%A0%E5%B0%9A%E8%8A%B3&amp;rft.date=1991&amp;rft.volume=20&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=159%E2%80%93168&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.3406%2Fclao.1991.1345&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Old_Chinese"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
